content: The energy in NYC is electric. Just got back and already feel the buzz. And my favorite bodega on the corner is still there, serving the best egg and cheese on a roll.
Joined a meetup at a local tech hub. Lots of talk about AI in finance. Feeling inspired and out of my depth at the same time.
Spent the morning reviewing my trading algorithms. It's like trying to teach an old dog new tricks, but with code.
My birthday was a quiet affair. Had some friends over, reflected on the year. Realized how much I've learned, and how much more there is to go.
Set up a meeting with a quant trader I met at the tech hub. Going to discuss potential mentorship opportunities.
Dived into a deep learning course. My head hurts, but this is what growth feels like, right?
Went for a run in Central Park. Cleared my head. Came back with an idea for a new trading strategy. Sketching it out now.
Had that meeting with the quant trader. He's tough, but I'm in. Now I have a mentor to guide me through this labyrinth.
Spent the day coding. Trying to integrate AI models into my trading algorithms. It's slow going, but progress is progress.
Got feedback on my trading strategy. It needs work, but the core idea is there. Time to refine and test.
Joined a virtual trading simulation with other aspiring traders. It's like playing poker with everyone showing their cards.
Met with a few developers to discuss potential collaborations. We're brainstorming how to use AI for real-time market analysis.
Today's realization: trading isn't just about numbers; it's about understanding human behavior. The market is a massive psychology experiment.
Set up a small home office. Feels like I'm officially starting my journey to become a quant trader. The dream is taking shape.
Joined a networking event. Met someone from a hedge fund. We exchanged ideas about AI's role in financial markets. The connections are starting to pay off.
End of the week. Reflecting on my progress. I've learned so much, but every step forward feels like a small victory in this vast world of finance.
Had a breakthrough with the AI model. It now predicts market movements with 10% better accuracy. The grind is paying off.
Just got an email. My paper on AI in trading got accepted for a conference in Chicago. Guess who's presenting next month?
Went over my old trades. Found a pattern in my mistakes. Time to update the algorithm with these insights.
Long call with my mentor. He pointed out a flaw in my risk management strategy. Back to the drawing board.
First test run of the new risk management protocol. It held up better than expected. Small victories.
Discovered a new library for real-time data processing. Integrating it tonight. This could be a game-changer.
The conference prep is intense. Polished my presentation on how AI can predict market sentiment. Fingers crossed.
Met a neuroscientist at a networking event. Had a mind-blowing chat about cognitive enhancement. New connections forming.
Spent the day at the library. Diving into books on neural interfaces. The more I read, the more I see its potential in trading.
Set up a meeting with a cognitive psychologist. Want to explore how we can enhance decision-making in trading.
My trading buddy and I are now collaborating on an AI project. It's like having a partner in crime.
Just got feedback from the quant trader. He's impressed with my progress. Might be time to consider a formal partnership.
The AI model failed a stress test. Back to the code. Sometimes setbacks are just setups for comebacks.
Had a coffee with a potential collaborator. We're brainstorming a project to combine our AI models for better predictions.
Ran into an old friend from college. Turns out he's now a big shot in fintech. Invited me to join his think tank. Exciting times.
The conference is tomorrow. Last-minute tweaks to the presentation. Feeling the nerves, but ready to showcase my work.
Just had a breakthrough in the AI model's robustness. Tested it against historical market crashes, and it's holding up well. Slow and steady wins the race.
Had a meeting with my fintech friend. He's keen on our AI project. We're setting up a formal partnership agreement next week.
Got my hands on a quantum computing course. Diving into quantum-resistant algorithms. This is next-level stuff for secure blockchain transactions.
The new AI model tweak is now predicting market sentiment with 12% better accuracy. Just 3% away from the goal. This calls for a minor celebration.
Attended a seminar on AI ethics. Got some food for thought on how we should be ethically programming our models.
